title: Massey perfect in JV victories over Plainsmen
text:
Massey perfect in JV victories over Plainsmen By: Uncredited Report Error 
The Vincent Massey Vikings junior varsity boys’ and girls’ teams both won 3-0 sweeps against the visiting Crocus Plainsmen in the Westman High School Volleyball League on Wednesday night. 
In the boys’ match, Liam Nohr had 18 assists, three kills and four aces for Vincent Massey, which won 25-19, 25-18, 25-14. 
Brock Carmichael added seven kills and one block for the Vikings, while Braden Cancade had four kills, two blocks and one ace. 
Clayton Kreller had seven kills for Crocus. 
In the JV girls’ match, James DeGroot had nine kills and six digs as the Vikings beat the Plainsmen 25-15, 25-11, 25-14. Jayden Miller contributed five kills for the winners, while Logan Wallace had four kills and eight digs. 
Hallie Unger had 10 digs and an ace for Crocus, while Alexa Nepinak had five kills and eight digs.
